natural solution: Consider the triangle with angle 4; label the other two angles angle 5 and angle 6.

By triangle angle-sum, $m\angle1+m\angle2+m\angle3+m\angle5+m\angle6=180^{\circ}$, or \[ m\angle5+m\angle6=180^{\circ}-76^{\circ}-27^{\circ}-17^{\circ}=60^{\circ} \] By triangle angle-sum on the small triangle, $m\angle4+m\angle5+m\angle6=180^{\circ}$, so $60^{\circ}+m\angle4=180^{\circ}$ or $m\angle4=\boxed{120^{\circ}}$.
